❌ Downtime difference!
❌ Which is DEFAULT strategy?

There are 2 deployment strategies:
Rolling Update — K8s creates new pods one by one with updated image and slowly kills old pods. 
No downtime! App is always available during update. 
This is the default strategy in Kubernetes!
Recreate — K8s kills ALL old pods first, then creates new pods. This causes
downtime — app is unavailable for some time. 
Used when old and new versions cannot run at the same time
Easy way to remember:
Rolling Update = Train moving 🚂
                 new coaches added
                 old coaches removed
                 train never stops!
                 NO downtime! ✅

Recreate       = Bus stop 🚌
                 old bus leaves first
                 wait for new bus
                 passengers wait!
                 DOWNTIME! ❌

